  </owl:ObjectProperty>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/PM-14">
    <rdfs:comment>A directly-originated private loan — the borrower, the facility terms, the covenants, the drawn / undrawn position, the interest accrual, the workout state. The post-close lifecycle entity for direct private credit, modelling the loan as it lives between origination and either repayment or recovery.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>PM-14 Direct Loan</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/E-02"/>
  </owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/E-10">
    <rdfs:comment>A benchmark or index, and its constituents, held as managed reference data. The comparator a portfolio or holding's performance is measured against.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>E-10 Benchmark / Index</rdfs:label>
    <skos:closeMatch rdf:resource="https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/fibo-ind-mkt-bas/"/>
  </owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/E-13">
    <rdfs:comment>A name a master record has been seen under. The structure that makes entity resolution work — fed by the resolution feedback loop, read by it on the next cycle.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>E-13 Entity Alias</rdfs:label>
  </owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/PM-05">
    <rdfs:comment>The legal structure through which an investor holds a private investment — the layer between the fund investment (PM-09) and the cash flows. Cash flows are recorded at vehicle grain and aggregate up to the investment.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>PM-05 Legal Vehicle / SPV</rdfs:label>
  </owl:Class>
  <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/borrower-in">
    <rdfs:comment>Inverse of openim:has-borrower (role, n-to-1).</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/E-01"/>
    <rdfs:label>BORROWER_IN</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:range>
      <owl:Class rdf:nodeID="cb1b52746d9f86b323aaa61cd2305e4bb74c20d8cec8528c3603ef14f24425bdf82">
        <owl:unionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
          <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/PB-10"/>
          <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/PM-14"/>
        </owl:unionOf>
      </owl:Class>
    </rdfs:range>
    <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/openim/ontology/has-borrower"/>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
